'''Anatol Vieru''' ({{IPA-ro|anaˈtol viˈeru}}; 8 June 1926 – 8 October 1998) was a [[Music theory|music theoretician]], influential pedagogue, and a leading [[Romanian people|Romanian]]-Jewish<ref>http://www.romanianjewish.org/db/pdf/nr254_255/pagina19.pdf</ref> composer of the 20th century.  A pupil of [[Aram Khachaturian]], he composed seven symphonies, eight string quartets, numerous concertos, and much chamber music. He also wrote three [[operas]]: ''Iona'' (1976), ''Praznicul Calicilor'' (1981), and ''Telegrame, Tema si Variatiuni'' (1983).  He was awarded the [[Herder Prize]] in 1986.<ref>[http://opera.stanford.edu/composers/V.html Opera Glass]</ref>

