[[File:Johann Heinrich Hübschmann.jpg|thumb|Johann Heinrich Hübschmann.]] '''Johann Heinrich Hübschmann''' (1 July 1848 – 20 January 1908) was a [[Germans|German]] [[philology|philologist]].
==Life== He born on July 1, 1848 at [[Erfurt]]. He studied Oriental philology at [[Friedrich Schiller University of Jena|Jena]], [[Eberhard Karls University of Tübingen|Tübingen]], [[University of Leipzig|Leipzig]], and [[Ludwig Maximilians University of Munich|Munich]]; in 1876 became [[professor]] of Iranian languages at Leipzig, and in 1877 professor of comparative philology at [[University of Strasbourg|Strassburg]]. Hübschmann died on January 20, 1908 in [[Freiburg im Breisgau]].
==Research on Armenian== Hübschmann was the first to show in 1875 that the [[Armenian language]] was not a branch of the [[Iranian languages]] (earlier assumed so because of the immense amount of Iranian influence on Armenian throughout its history) but an entirely separate [[Indo-European languages|Indo-European]] branch in its own right.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utexas.edu/cola/centers/lrc/books/read12.html |title=A Reader in Nineteenth Century Historical Indo-European Linguistics: On the Position of Armenian in the Sphere of the Indo-European Languages |publisher=Utexas.edu |date=20 March 2007 |accessdate=9 December 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151221145559/http://www.utexas.edu/cola/centers/lrc/books/read12.html |archivedate=21 December 2015 |df= }}</ref>{{Better source|reason=Dead link to a web page version of a chapter published in "A Reader in Nineteenth Century Historical Indo-European Linguistics" (1967)|date=October 2016}} He used the [[comparative method]] to separate the Iranian loanwords, which make up the majority of Armenian words, from an older layer of native Armenian words.<ref name="iranicaonline.org">{{cite encyclopedia |last1=Schmitt |first1=Rüdiger |author-link1=Rudiger Schmitt |last2=Bailey |first2=Harold Walter |author-link2=Harold Walter Bailey |editor-last=Yarshater |editor-first=Ehsan |editor-link=Ehsan Yarshater |encyclopedia=[[Encyclopædia Iranica]] |title=Iranian influences in Armenian Language |url=http://www.iranicaonline.org/articles/armenia-iv |access-date=9 December 2015 |date=2011 |orig-year=1986 |publisher=Encyclopædia Iranica Foundation |edition=Online |quote=The revolutionary element in Hübschmann’s procedure was that according to him Arm. words fully or largely agreeing with Ir. forms in phonetic shape were suspect of being loanwords and could therefore not safely be regarded as genuine Arm. words. It was due to this methodological principle, which only gradually gained universal acceptance, that Hübschmann became the significant pioneer in the study of Ir. borrowings in Armenian. |last-author-amp=yes}}</ref>
==Works== *"Ueber die Stellung des Armenischen im Kreise der indogermanischen Sprachen" (1875) *''Armenische Studien'' (1883) *''Das indogermanische Vokalsystem (1885) *''Etymologie und Lautlehre der ossetischen Sprache'' (1887) *''Persische Studien'' (1895) * ''Armenische Grammatik. I. Theil. Armenische Etymologie. I. Abtheilung: Die persischen und arabischen Lehnwörter im Altarmenischen.'' Leipzig, 1895 ** ''Armenische Grammatik. I. Theil. Armenische Etymologie'' (Bibliothek indogermanischer Grammatiken. Band VI), Leipzig, 1897 *''Altarmenische Ortsnamen'' (1904)
