{{Commons category|Nuribta letter 365 (Amarna letter)}}
'''Nuribta''', also '''Nuribda''', was a city, or [[city-state]] located in the vicinity of [[Megiddo (place)|Magiddo]] in Israel, in historical [[Canaan]] during the time of the [[Amarna letters]] [[Text corpus|correspondence]], a 15-20 year [[Time period|period]] of about [[1350 BC|1350]]-[[1335 BC]].
The majority of the Amarna letters were written to the [[pharaoh]] of [[Ancient Egypt]] and the only reference to ''Naribta'' is a letter by [[Biridiya]] of ''Magidda'', EA 365, entitled: ''"Furnishing corvée workers"'', ([[EA (el Amarna)|EA]] is for 'el [[Amarna]]').
==A letter of [[corvée]] work==
===EA 365, Biridiya letter no. 7 of 7 ''"Furnishing corvée workers"''=== :'''"Say [to the ki]ng-(i.e. [[pharaoh]]), my lord and my [Su]n: Message of [[Biridiya]], the loyal servant of the king. I [[Prostration formula|fall at the feet]] of the king, my lord and my Sun, 7 times and 7 times.''' :'''"May the king, my lord, take cognizance of his servant and his city. In fact, only I am [[Harvest|cultivating]]:''' ''[[ah (cuneiform)|ah]]-[[ri (cuneiform)|ri]]-[[šu (cuneiform)|šu]]'' '''in [[Shunem|Šunama]]-([[Shunem]]), and only I am furnishing corvée workers. But consider the mayors that are near me. They do not act as I do. They do not cultivate in Šunama, and they do not furnish corvée workers. Only I&ndash;''' ''ia<sub>8</sub>-[[hu (cuneiform)|hu]]-[[du (cuneiform)|du]]-[[un (cuneiform)|un]]-[[ni (cuneiform)|ni]]'' '''(by myself) furnish [[corvée]] workers. From [[Yapu (city near Magiddo-place)|Yapu]] they come, from [''' ''my''] ''resources'' '''here, (and) from ''Nuribta''. And may the king, my lord, take cognizance of his city."''' -EA 365, lines 1-31 (complete)
==See also== *[[corvée]] *[[Biridiya]] *[[Megiddo (place)]] *[[Amarna letters]] *[[Amarna letters–localities and their rulers]]
