{{italic title}}
'''''The Adventure of Archaeology''''' ({{ISBN|978-0-87044-603-0}}) is a 1985 book written by Dr. [[Brian M. Fagan]], published by the [[National Geographic Magazine|National Geographic]] press publishing company. The book tells about the development of the history of archeology. It contains stories of [[treasure hunting|treasure hunter]]s and tourists and the development of archeology to a [[scientific fields|scientific field]].<ref name=thegreatcourses>{{cite web|title=Human Prehistory and the First Civilizations|url=http://www.thegreatcourses.com.au/tgc/courses/course_detail.aspx?cid=380|publisher=thegreatcourses.com.au|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref> <ref name=bradshawfoundation.com>{{cite web|title=Beyond the Blue Horizon|url=http://www.bradshawfoundation.com/books/beyond_the_blue_horizon.php|publisher=bradshawfoundation.com|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref> <ref name=librarything>{{cite web|title=The Adventure of Archaeology|url=http://www.librarything.com/work/495169|publisher=librarything.com|accessdate=9 February 2014}}</ref>

